eva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">15.2k</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":15205,\"repo\":\"cjbarber/ToolsOfTheTrade\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--></strong></p>\n<p>Spectacular list of categorized tools for developers resulting from HackerNews threads. By <a href=\"https://twitter.com/chrisbarber\">Chris Barber</a> and <a href=\"https://twitter.com/davisonio\">Craig Davison</a>.</p>\n</li>","updatedAt":"2017-05-05T12:16:52.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"mezod/awesome-indie","categoryHTML":"<h3>Tools</h3>","itemHTML":"<li>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://github.com/Kickball/awesome-selfhosted\">awesome-selfhosted</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/Kickball/awesome-selfhosted\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">58.5k</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":58532,\"repo\":\"Kickball/awesome-selfhosted\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--></strong></p>\n<p>\"This is a list of Free Software network services and web applications which can be hosted locally. Selfhosting is the process of locally hosting and managing applications instead of renting from SaaS providers.\" Lots of salvageable software :P by <a href=\"https://github.com/Kickball\">Edward D</a>.</p>\n</li>","updatedAt":"2017-05-05T12:16:52.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"mezod/awesome-indie","categoryHTML":"<h3>Talks</h3>","itemHTML":"<li>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=0CDXJ6bMkMY\">David Heinemeier Hansson at Startup School 08</a></strong> by <a href=\"https://twitter.com/dhh\">David Heinemeier Hansson</a></p>\n<p>Bootstrapping as the better alternative to VC funded startups.</p>\n</li>","updatedAt":"2017-05-05T12:00:01.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"mezod/awesome-indie","categoryHTML":"<h3>Talks</h3>","itemHTML":"<li>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=i3d1asTrWUQ\">Tyler Tringas on Storemapper and MicroSaaS</a></strong> by <a href=\"https://twitter.com/tylertringas\">Tyler Tringas</a></p>\n<p>15 minutes filled with a lot of valuable information and insights where Tyler presents the concept of Micro-SaaS and tells us his story.</p>\n</li>","updatedAt":"2017-05-05T12:00:01.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"mezod/awesome-indie","categoryHTML":"<h3>Talks</h3>","itemHTML":"<li>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=m3nb_Qj3mRA\">Bootstrapping Side Projects To Profit by Pieter Levels</a></strong> by <a href=\"https://twitter.com/levelsio\">Pieter Levels</a></p>\n<p>Probably one of the most known indie hackers of the last couple of years talks about how to turn our side-projects into profitable businesses. Very straight to the point, Pieter always provides a lot of insightful thoughts. By the way, don't get fooled by his lifestyle, his success is 500% work.</p>\n</li>","updatedAt":"2017-05-05T12:00:01.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"mezod/awesome-indie","categoryHTML":"<h3>Talks</h3>","itemHTML":"<li>\n<p><strong><a href=\"http://businessofsoftware.org/2011/03/hello-ladies-patrick-mckenzie-at-business-of-software-2010-marketing-to-minorities/\">Marketing for Minorities</a></strong> by <a href=\"https://twitter.com/patio11?lang=ca\">Patrick McKenzie</a></p>\n<p>Lightning 7-minute talk by one of the most respected indie developers. The point Patrick is trying to make, is that solo developers can target way smaller and niche markets which might have low competition and be very profitable from a solo business point of view.</p>\n</li>","updatedAt":"2017-05-05T12:00:01.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"mezod/awesome-indie","categoryHTML":"<h3>Talks</h3>","itemHTML":"<li>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=J8UwcyYT3z0\">Talking about CoderPad and business at Dropbox</a></strong> by <a href=\"https://twitter.com/fulligin?lang=ca\">Vincent Woo</a></p>\n<p>Talk on building a successful small solo business.</p>\n</li>","updatedAt":"2017-05-05T12:00:01.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"mezod/awesome-indie","categoryHTML":"<h5>Other</h5>","itemHTML":"<li><strong><a href=\"https://vimeo.com/user12790628/videos\">Talks from the MicroConf</a></strong></li>","updatedAt":"2017-05-05T12:00:01.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"mezod/awesome-indie","categoryHTML":"<h5>Other</h5>","itemHTML":"<li><strong><a href=\"http://baconbiz.com/\">Talks from the BaconBizConf</a></strong></li>","updatedAt":"2017-05-05T12:00:01.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"mezod/awesome-indie","categoryHTML":"<h5>Other</h5>","itemHTML":"<li><strong><a href=\"http://businessofsoftware.org/2016/07/all-talks-from-business-of-software-conferences-in-one-place-saas-software-talks/\">Talks from Business of Software</a></strong></li>","updatedAt":"2017-05-05T12:00:01.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"mezod/awesome-indie","categoryHTML":"<h3>Posts</h3>","itemHTML":"<li>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://levels.io/12-startups-12-months/\">I’m Launching 12 Startups in 12 Months</a></strong> by <a href=\"https://twitter.com/levelsio\">Pieter Levels</a></p>\n<p>The challenge that started it all for Pieter. It inspired me to do something similar. What matters is to create and ship a lot, learning in the process, until something is worth pushing further.</p>\n</li>","updatedAt":"2017-05-05T12:00:01.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"mezod/awesome-indie","categoryHTML":"<h3>Posts</h3>","itemHTML":"<li>\n<p><strong><a href=\"http://www.kalzumeus.com/2011/10/28/dont-call-yourself-a-programmer/\">Don't Call Yourself A Programmer, And Other Career Advice</a></strong> by <a href=\"https://twitter.com/patio11?lang=ca\">Patrick McKenzie</a></p>\n<p>Patrick has written over 500 posts and I have obviously not read all of them, but of the many I've read, I chose this one...</p>\n</li>","updatedAt":"2017-05-05T12:00:01.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"mezod/awesome-indie","categoryHTML":"<h3>Posts</h3>","itemHTML":"<li>\n<p><strong><a href=\"http://www.kalzumeus.com/2010/03/20/running-a-software-business-on-5-hours-a-week/\">Running A Software Business On 5 Hours A Week</a></strong> by <a href=\"https://twitter.com/patio11?lang=ca\">Patrick McKenzie</a></p>\n<p>...and this one too :D</p>\n</li>","updatedAt":"2017-05-05T12:00:01.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"mezod/awesome-indie","categoryHTML":"<h3>Posts</h3>","itemHTML":"<li>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://tylertringas.com/storemapper-bootstrapped-to-50000year-in-2-years-with-live-metrics/\">Storemapper: Bootstrapped to $50,000/year in 2 years (with live metrics)</a></strong> by <a href=\"https://twitter.com/tylertringas\">Tyler Tringas</a></p>\n<p>This is just an example of a business more than one would be happy with :-) Besides liking how Tyler shares his story building Storemapper, I think he always maximizes for valuable content.</p>\n</li>","updatedAt":"2017-05-05T12:00:01.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"mezod/awesome-indie","categoryHTML":"<h3>Posts</h3>","itemHTML":"<li>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://unicornfree.com/2013/why-you-should-do-a-tiny-product-first\">Why You Should Do A Tiny Product First</a></strong> by <a href=\"https://twitter.com/amyhoy\">Amy Hoy</a></p>\n<p>This is the first of a series by Amy Hoy. I'll be honest, I don't even remember what this was about, just that I found it worth my time. Oh wait, yeah, Amy told me not to code, at least at first. I haven't still gotten there...</p>\n</li>","updatedAt":"2017-05-05T12:00:01.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"mezod/awesome-indie","categoryHTML":"<h3>Posts</h3>","itemHTML":"<li>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://medium.com/@cliffordoravec/the-epic-guide-to-bootstrapping-a-saas-startup-from-scratch-by-yourself-part-1-4d834e1df8c1\">The Epic Guide to Bootstrapping a SaaS Startup from Scratch — By Yourself</a></strong> by <a href=\"https://twitter.com/cliffordoravec\">Clifford Oravec</a></p>\n<p>Another series on what solo bootstrapping is about, with an offensive twist.</p>\n</li>","updatedAt":"2017-05-05T12:00:01.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"mezod/awesome-indie","categoryHTML":"<h3>Posts</h3>","itemHTML":"<li>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://medium.com/product-people/how-to-get-more-customers-54f64220e430\">How to get more customers</a></strong> by <a href=\"https://twitter.com/mijustin\">Justin Jackson</a>.</p>\n<p>This is a bit of a too specific topic for this general selection of posts, but the hell, you need to read it before it's too late. Ok, I'm starting to sound marketingy :D</p>\n</li>","updatedAt":"2017-05-05T12:00:01.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"mezod/awesome-indie","categoryHTML":"<h3>Posts</h3>","itemHTML":"<li>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://hackernoon.com/indie-startups-the-ingredients-of-success-74531fe3a019\">Indie Startups: The Ingredients of Success</a></strong> by <a href=\"https://hackernoon.com/@fpgaminer\">fpgaminer</a></p>\n<p>Numbers with meaning. fpgaminer analyzed all the products featured on IndieHackers, extracted some statistics and got to some conclusions. Also worth reading for the approach.</p>\n</li>","updatedAt":"2017-05-05T12:00:01.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"mezod/awesome-indie","categoryHTML":"<h5>Others</h5>","itemHTML":"<li><strong><a href=\"https://bootstrappers.io/\">Bootstrappers.io</a></strong></li>","updatedAt":"2017-05-05T12:00:01.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"mezod/awesome-indie","categoryHTML":"<h5>Others</h5>","itemHTML":"<li><strong><a href=\"https://hackernoon.com/\">HackerNoon</a></strong></li>","updatedAt":"2017-05-05T12:00:01.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"mezod/awesome-indie","categoryHTML":"<h5>Others</h5>","itemHTML":"<li><strong><a href=\"https://news.ycombinator.com/\">HackerNews</a></strong></li>","updatedAt":"2017-05-05T12:00:01.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"mezod/awesome-indie","categoryHTML":"<h5>Others</h5>","itemHTML":"<li><strong><a href=\"https://hackernoon.com/7-articles-for-indie-devs-to-start-shipping-12b22f5e5660\">7 Articles for Indie Devs to Start Shipping</a></strong> - great selection by <a href=\"https://twitter.com/mskvsk\">Alex Moskovski</a></li>","updatedAt":"2017-05-05T12:00:01.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"mezod/awesome-indie","categoryHTML":"<h3>Blogs</h3>","itemHTML":"<li>\n<p><strong><a href=\"http://www.kalzumeus.com/\">Patrick Mackenzie</a></strong></p>\n<p>Over 500 posts that show how Patrick went from being a software engineer to running successful software businesses.</p>\n</li>","updatedAt":"2017-05-05T12:00:01.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"mezod/awesome-indie","categoryHTML":"<h3>Blogs</h3>","itemHTML":"<li>\n<p><strong><a href=\"http://www.softwarebyrob.com/\">Rob Walling</a></strong></p>\n<p>Lessons Learned by a Solo Entrepreneur.</p>\n</li>","updatedAt":"2017-05-05T12:00:01.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"mezod/awesome-indie","categoryHTML":"<h3>Blogs</h3>","itemHTML":"<li>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://levels.io/\">Pieter Levels</a></strong></p>\n<p>Lots of advice on bootstrapping businesses if you dig between Pieter's multiple interests.</p>\n</li>","updatedAt":"2017-05-05T12:00:01.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"mezod/awesome-indie","categoryHTML":"<h3>Blogs</h3>","itemHTML":"<li>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://tylertringas.com/\">Tyler Tringas</a></strong></p>\n<p>On SaaS and his journey with Storemapper.</p>\n</li>","updatedAt":"2017-05-05T12:00:01.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"mezod/awesome-indie","categoryHTML":"<h3>Blogs</h3>","itemHTML":"<li>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://www.joelonsoftware.com/\">Joel Spolsky</a></strong></p>\n<p>Software and business have always been topics Joel has covered. StackOverflow and Trello prove he knows what he's talking about.</p>\n</li>","updatedAt":"2017-05-05T12:00:01.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"mezod/awesome-indie","categoryHTML":"<h3>Blogs</h3>","itemHTML":"<li>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://m.signalvnoise.com/\">Signal v. Noise</a></strong></p>\n<p>The blog of the basecamp people, mostly David Heinemeier Hansson and Jason Fried, on business and how to run bootstrapped companies.</p>\n</li>","updatedAt":"2017-05-05T12:00:01.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"mezod/awesome-indie","categoryHTML":"<h3>Blogs</h3>","itemHTML":"<li>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://blog.pinboard.in/\">Pinboard</a></strong></p>\n<p>Maciej Cegłowski's blog for his bookmarking tool, pinboard, useful in showing the growth of a successful solo business.</p>\n</li>","updatedAt":"2017-05-05T12:00:01.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"mezod/awesome-indie","categoryHTML":"<h5>Others</h5>","itemHTML":"<li><strong><a href=\"https://thefoundation.com/blog\">The Foundation</a></strong> - Turning the process of creating a B2B SaaS business into a formula.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-05-05T12:00:01.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"mezod/awesome-indie","categoryHTML":"<h5>Others</h5>","itemHTML":"<li><strong><a href=\"http://www.priceintelligently.com/blog\">Price Intelligently</a></strong> - Blog focused on the economics of the SaaS business model and SaaS pricing.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-05-05T12:00:01.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"mezod/awesome-indie","categoryHTML":"<h5>Others</h5>","itemHTML":"<li><strong><a href=\"https://moz.com/blog\">Moz Blog</a></strong> - For anything related to SEO.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-05-05T12:00:01.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"mezod/awesome-indie","categoryHTML":"<h5>Others</h5>","itemHTML":"<li><strong><a href=\"http://www.paulgraham.com/articles.html\">Paul Graham</a></strong> - A lot of content for big funded startups, but still relevant to bootstrappers.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-05-05T12:00:01.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"mezod/awesome-indie","categoryHTML":"<h5>Others</h5>","itemHTML":"<li><strong><a href=\"https://john.onolan.org/\">John O'Nolan</a></strong> - Especially the older posts on how he started ghost.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-05-05T12:00:01.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"mezod/awesome-indie","categoryHTML":"<h3>Case Studies</h3>","itemHTML":"<li>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://www.indiehackers.com/blog\">IndieHackers</a></strong></p>\n<p>From capturing a trend to getting acquired in less than one year.</p>\n</li>","updatedAt":"2017-05-05T12:00:01.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"mezod/awesome-indie","categoryHTML":"<h3>Case Studies</h3>","itemHTML":"<li>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://levels.io/product-hunt-hacker-news-number-one/\">NomadList</a></strong></p>\n<p>Solving your own pain, representing a movement, moving fast and working hard by a serial bootstrapper.</p>\n</li>","updatedAt":"2017-05-05T12:00:01.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"mezod/awesome-indie","categoryHTML":"<h3>Case Studies</h3>","itemHTML":"<li>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://www.bugmuncher.com/blog/\">Bugmuncher</a></strong></p>\n<p>Transparent growth and financial reports by a solo saas founder.</p>\n</li>","updatedAt":"2017-05-05T12:00:01.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"mezod/awesome-indie","categoryHTML":"<h3>Case Studies</h3>","itemHTML":"<li>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://baremetrics.com/blog\">Baremetrics</a></strong></p>\n<p>An example of riding the wave.</p>\n</li>","updatedAt":"2017-05-05T12:00:01.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"mezod/awesome-indie","categoryHTML":"<h3>Events</h3>","itemHTML":"<li>\n<p><strong><a href=\"http://www.microconf.com/\">MicroConf</a></strong> [$]</p>\n<p>\"The world's biggest conference for the world's smallest self-funded software companies\". It has two editions, one more focused to starters, and another one focused on growth. Both last two days. Las Vegas. Run by <a href=\"https://twitter.com/robwalling\">Rob Walling</a> and <a href=\"https://twitter.com/SingleFounder\">Mike Taber</a>.</p>\n</li>","updatedAt":"2017-05-05T12:00:01.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"mezod/awesome-indie","categoryHTML":"<h3>Events</h3>","itemHTML":"<li>\n<p><strong><a href=\"http://www.microconfeurope.com/\">MicroConf Europe</a></strong> [$]</p>\n<p>MicroConf's European edition. Barcelona. Run by <a href=\"https://twitter.com/robwalling\">Rob Walling</a> and <a href=\"https://twitter.com/SingleFounder\">Mike Taber</a>.</p>\n</li>","updatedAt":"2017-05-05T12:00:01.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"mezod/awesome-indie","categoryHTML":"<h3>Events</h3>","itemHTML":"<li>\n<p><strong><a href=\"http://baconbiz.com/\">BaconBizConf</a></strong> [$]</p>\n<p>\"An alliance for B2B bootstrappers\". Philadelphia. By <a href=\"https://twitter.com/amyhoy\">Amy Hoy</a> and <a href=\"https://twitter.com/alexhillman\">Alex Hillman</a>.</p>\n</li>","updatedAt":"2017-05-05T12:00:01.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"mezod/awesome-indie","categoryHTML":"<h5>Not specific to indie founders:</h5>","itemHTML":"<li>\n<p><strong><a href=\"http://businessofsoftware.org/\">Business of Software</a></strong> [$]</p>\n<p>\"Business of Software is not based in Silicon Valley for good reason. It is about building long term, sustainable software businesses. …a thoughtful conference, where people come to listen and learn, not self promote and shout\". Boston. <a href=\"http://thebln.com/team/\">Team behind BoS</a>.</p>\n</li>","updatedAt":"2017-05-05T12:00:01.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"mezod/awesome-indie","categoryHTML":"<h5>Not specific to indie founders:</h5>","itemHTML":"<li>\n<p><strong><a href=\"http://businessofsoftware.eu/\">Business of Software Europe</a></strong> [$]</p>\n<p>BoS European edition. London. <a href=\"http://thebln.com/team/\">Team behind BoS</a>.</p>\n</li>","updatedAt":"2017-05-05T12:00:01.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"mezod/awesome-indie","categoryHTML":"<h5>Not specific to indie founders:</h5>","itemHTML":"<li>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://b2brocks.co/\">B2B Rocks</a></strong> [$]</p>\n<p>\"Leading conferences for B2B and SaaS startups\". Popular business model for indie devs. Paris. Sydney.</p>\n</li>","updatedAt":"2017-05-05T12:00:01.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"mezod/awesome-indie","categoryHTML":"<h5>Not specific to indie founders:</h5>","itemHTML":"<li>\n<p><strong><a href=\"http://peersconf.com/\">PeersConf</a></strong> [$]</p>\n<p>\"A conference for those who make the web, and make it their business\". Seattle (changes every year). By <a href=\"https://twitter.com/justjessdc\">Jessica D'Amico</a>.</p>\n</li>","updatedAt":"2017-05-05T12:00:01.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"mezod/awesome-indie","categoryHTML":"<h3>Books</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><strong><a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/Start-Small-Stay-Developers-Launching-ebook/dp/B003YH9MMI/ref=sr_1_1?s=digital-text&#x26;ie=UTF8&#x26;qid=1493983910&#x26;sr=1-1&#x26;keywords=start+small+stay+small\">Start Small, Stay Small</a></strong> [$] by <a href=\"https://twitter.com/robwalling\">Rob Walling</a>.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-05-05T12:00:01.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"mezod/awesome-indie","categoryHTML":"<h3>Books</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><strong><a href=\"http://www.singlefounderhandbook.com/\">The Single Founder Handbook</a></strong> [$] by <a href=\"https://twitter.com/SingleFounder\">Mike Taber</a>.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-05-05T12:00:01.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"mezod/awesome-indie","categoryHTML":"<h5>Other</h5>","itemHTML":"<li><strong><a href=\"http://thesaasbootstrapper.com/book-list/\">The SaaS Bootstrapper book list</a></strong> - Collection curated by <a href=\"http://macmartine.com/\">Mac Martine</a>.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-05-05T12:00:01.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"mezod/awesome-indie","categoryHTML":"<h5>Other</h5>","itemHTML":"<li><strong><a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/dp/B00SI0B5FS/ref=dp-kindle-redirect?_encoding=UTF8&#x26;btkr=1\">Anything You Want</a></strong> [$] by <a href=\"https://twitter.com/sivers\">Derek Sivers</a>.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-05-05T12:00:01.